<REFENTRY id="split">
<REFMETA><REFENTRYTITLE>
split
</REFENTRYTITLE></REFMETA>
<REFNAMEDIV>
<REFNAME>split</REFNAME>
<REFPURPOSE>
split a file into pieces
</REFPURPOSE>
</REFNAMEDIV>
<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>Description</TITLE>
<PARA>
<COMMAND>split</COMMAND> is as specified in the Single UNIX
Specification but with
differences as listed below.
</PARA>
</REFSECT1>

<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>Differences</TITLE>
<VARIABLELIST>

<VARLISTENTRY>
<TERM>-a suffix_length</TERM>
<LISTITEM>
<PARA>
has unspecified behavior.
<FOOTNOTE>
<PARA>
Newer versions of split in GNU textutils have support for the -a
flag.  In a future version of the LSB, the -a flag shall be required to
conform to the Single UNIX Specification definition.
</PARA>
</FOOTNOTE>
</PARA>
</LISTITEM>
</VARLISTENTRY>

</VARIABLELIST>
</REFSECT1>

</REFENTRY>
